The paper discusses coalgebraic characterizations of context-free languages, which is a topic in theoretical computer science. The paper uses concepts from formal language theory, algebra, and coalgebra. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), which deals with the use of logic in computer science, including formal language theory. The paper also discusses formal power series, which falls under the sub-category cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). The paper also uses concepts from algebra and coalgebra, which are covered in the sub-categories cs.PL (Programming Languages), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.THEORY (Theoretical Computer Science).
